io.oasp.module.service.common.base.config

Class ServiceConfigProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.oasp.module.service.common.base.config.ServiceConfigProperties
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ServiceConfig

    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix="")
public class ServiceConfigProperties
extends Object
implements ServiceConfig
    Implementation of ServiceConfig as spring-boot ConfigurationProperties.
    Assuming you would have the following in your application.properties: 
     service.client.app.foo.url=https://foo.company.com/services/rest
 service.client.app.bar.url=https://bar.company.com/services/rest
 service.client.default.url=https://api.company.com/services/rest
    Then asClientConfig().getValue(ServiceConfig.KEY_SEGMENT_APP, "foo", ServiceConfig.KEY_SEGMENT_URL) would return "https://foo.company.com/services/rest". This URL would be used by ServiceDiscovererImplConfig for a Service of the application "foo". For a Service of the application "some" the URL "https://api.company.com/services/rest" would be used as default because no property "service.client.app.some.url" is defined.
    Since:
    3.0.0
